THE younger ones may not know Chief Mrs. Modupe Sagoe but her pedigree as one of Nigeria’s foremost textile merchants remain valid. Sagoe, who is popular for her HOH Swiss headgear, Gele Sagoe, enjoyed immense love and support during her birthday celebration recently in Lagos.   Alex-Duduyemi opens new house     Daughter remembers Ndubuisi Kanu     Alapini throws classy birthday bash   Also, a thanksgiving service was held in honour of Sisi Modupe Sagoe at the Cathedral Church of Christ in Marina, Lagos. Sagoe is from the Thomas family of Lagos Island. Her step-mother was the granddaughter of the late Candido Da Rocha, a business mogul. Her highly respected lawyer husband, Taiwo Sagoe, died in December 2012 at 85. The union was blessed with three children – Ekua Abudu-Akinsanya, Kofi Sagoe and Araba Morakinyo.